> To: Dasovich, Jeff; mbaldwin@igservice.com; Hass, Glen
> Cc: Harris, Steven
> Subject: I9907003 Ruling re Notice of a Full Panel Hearing
>
>
> Team,
> Looks like things are finally coming home to roost here.  I would argue
> that we (TW and Enron) should both consider getting our 5-minute sound
> bite in here since we're being afforded the opportunity.  Obviously, our
> goal should be to see the Commission adopt the Comprehensive Settlement.
> Our focus point during our presentation should be on not only the
> sufficiency of infrastructure (not dealt with specfically in the
> Comprehensive Settlement) but the idea that there must be a concomitant
> unbundling of the intrastate transmission and a rational, equitable
> means to allocate capacity at receipt points and an orderly assignment
> of firm rights to shippers (primary/secondary).  Let's put together a
> short teleconference to work out our strategy here and make sure we're
> on the agenda for May 22.
>
> Will you guys send me a note back and let me know your availabilty Mon.,
> Tues. or Wed.?
